-- ISRAEL DAYBOOK: IDB Holding’s Rating Lowered by S&P Maalot
-- B y   D a v i d   W a i n e r
-- 2012-05-14T05:43:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/israel-daybook-idb-holding-s-rating-lowered-by-s-p-maalot.html
IDB Holding Corp. said Standard &
Poor’s Maalot lowered its rating to ilBBB- from ilA- and that of
IDB Development Corp. was cut to ilBBB+ from ilA-.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* The Finance Ministry is planning to sell a combined 1.65
billion shekels ($431 million) at a bond auction today.  EQUITY MOVERS:
*  Ormat Industries Ltd. (ORMT)   reported a first-quarter
profit of $5.8 million after a loss of $3.45 million in the
year-earlier period. The developer of geothermal plants said
revenue rose to $132.4 million from $99.1 million.
*  RadVision Ltd. (RVSN)  , the maker of video-conferencing
systems, will announce first-quarter results today.  MARKETS:
* The  TA-25 Index (TA-25)  declined 0.6 percent to 1,127.91 yesterday
* The yield on the Mimshal Shiklit government bond due January
2022 was at 4.53 percent.
* The shekel weakened 0.3 percent to 3.8261 a dollar at 8:20
a.m. in Tel Aviv.
* Corn for July delivery rose 0.3 percent to $5.8275 a bushel.
* Crude oil for June delivery declined 0.5 percent to $95.70 a
barrel.
* Gold for immediate delivery gained 0.1 percent to $1,581.27
an ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
